==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Husking
<hw>Husk"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
or process of stripping off husks, as from Indian corn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A meeting of neighbors or friends to assist in
husking maize; -- called also</def> <xex>husking bee</xex>.
<mark>[U.S.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A red ear in the <xex>husking</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Husky</ent>⟦br⟧
